rComments: He uploaded videos explaining the materials. In the class, he only answered questions. I didn't have enough background and there were no homework or quizzes only two exams and a final project. I had to read the book apart from watching the videos and also study the algorithms on youtube as sometimes the examples were not clear enough
teacherRatingTags: ['Test heavy', 'Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: I found this course fun and I think Prof. Zaguia taught it well. He uploaded videos explaining the course material and we asked our questions during class hours. Videos were clear but he would explain again if someone asked. We had 2 midterms, 4 assignments and a final, which I found not so difficult. He is so nice and wants his students to pass.

Perhaps it was the online class format, but I found the structure unreasonably demanding on students. Mostly he was inaccessible outside of a few "sessions" that he didn't always show up to. Pretty disorganised and altogether felt a bit insulted to be paying for sub-standard teaching and service.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read', 'Test heavy']

rComments: This class didn't have mandatory attendance, which was nice, but lecture notes were downright terrible and useless. Luckily the midterms were totally easy, most students could pass with just the prerequisite class. Homework was very long and worth basically nothing (4 that were 2.5% each), so I never really cared about it much.
He is one of the best in uOttawa. I really recommend you take one of his courses because he actually teaches and interacts with students while teaching.

CSI3104 was not an easy course. The assignments were tricky, but the midterm was very easy if you reviewed the slides. Zaguia's organized and knowledgeable. I would take another class with him. I guess the one drawback is that he had a lot of difficulty with Brightspace.
This course is super difficult but the prof is nice and generous to give marks

The content and the exams are all difficult. The prof knows everything, but he can't teach well so that most people did really bad in the exams. However, it is said that he never failed any student for this course. By the way, I got 13/35 in the final but got A- in the end.

Pros: His lectures are organized and clear, and he uses good examples. He's a good public speaker. The assignments are challenging, but answers to similar problems can be found online. There were no surprises on the midterm. It was easy.  Cons: He isn't available outside of class or via email. I'd probably try a class in French if he were the prof.

The guy has been teaching the same classes for a long time. His lectures are clear and engaging, but he doesn't pretend to care about you.   If you're the kind of person that likes good lecturers and doesn't ask the prof for help, Nejib is for you. Otherwise, think twice about it.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Graded by few things', 'Participation matters']

rComments: I dropped the course after midterm because I could not handle the course with this professor. I guess this teacher is good for smart students who like difficult puzzles.

The course is interesting, if only the professor was more responsive to questions, or gave a feedback. No grading criteria either. The assignments are taken from a book and a very long and hard. TA is awful in marking and will take marks off for grammar, or for stapling the page wrong.

Its a good course from the knowledge it delivers. The professor gives clear and informative lecture to make sure that you understand the material. However, the TA who marks the asssignment will totally demolish your marks in every possible way, marks were taken because you don't put them in an envelope or you have a grammar mistake.

i wonder that if the TAs are really marking them or just randomly give marks. There were even some penalties for grammar or spelling mistakes in assignments  !!! you will see 'nonsense ' in ur assignments but u don't know why and the TAs will not explain the reasons.

Decent prof, although my issues with the class were with the assignments from the textbook, which are insanely difficult for the level of this course. They are designed to push and challenge you (and possibly balance your final mark with an absurdly easy midterm).
Best prof. ever. no doubt

Probably the worst professor I ever came across. The class is pretty much a maths course it used to be MAT2343 before. His lectures were auction houses, incomprehensible, pretty much gave his opinions on the things he put up on the slide. He likes to give you either 0 or full marks for all questions. So you will either fail this course or get an A

Very smooth voice, enjoyable lectures, easy material, but I didn't attend many lecturse. Her class missed several chapters due to his absences.

His idea of marking exams is to finish it all in one day. We had our exam on thursday night and the marks were up on Saturday.   Engineering students are too complacent.
